# C# simple properties: one line per property

When adding or editing **simple** auto-implemented properties (no custom accessor bodies, no `get =>` expression bodies), use a **single physical line** for the whole property declaration, including accessors.

## Do

```csharp
public Guid TenantId { get; set; }
public string? Name { get; init; }
public int Count { get; private set; }
AgentType AgentType { get; }
```

Keep optional attributes on the line(s) immediately above the property; the property line itself stays one line.

## Do not

Do not expand simple accessors across multiple lines:

```csharp
// Avoid
public Guid TenantId
{
    get; set;
}
```

## Adjacent properties: no blank line between

When two or more **consecutive** lines are each a **simple one-line** auto-property (`{ get; set; }`, `{ get; init; }`, `{ get; private set; }`, `{ get; }`, same line only), **do not** put empty lines between them. This keeps DTOs and models compact.

Keep a **blank line** before the next **different** member: methods, constructors, nested types, fields, expression-bodied members, or any property that is not a single-line simple auto-property.

### Do

```csharp
public string Application { get; init; } = string.Empty;
public string InformationalVersion { get; init; } = string.Empty;
public string? CommitSha { get; init; }

public static BuildInfoResponse FromProvenance(...)
{
    ...
}
```

### Do not

```csharp
// Avoid: blank lines only between adjacent simple one-line properties
public string Application { get; init; } = string.Empty;

public string InformationalVersion { get; init; } = string.Empty;
```

## Scope

- Applies to `get;` / `set;` / `init;` **auto-properties only**, on **one line**.
- Does **not** apply when either accessor has a body (`get { return ... }`, `get =>`, `set { ... }`).
- Indexers (`this[...]`), explicit interface implementations, and unusual modifiers follow normal C# formatting; if a property is too long for readability, prefer extracting types or using `required` / split lines on the **type** only when the team agrees—default remains one line for simple DTOs and models.

## Bulk fix

To re-normalize files after a bad merge, run from the repo root:

`python scripts/collapse_simple_properties.py`

That script:

- Collapses multiline blocks whose body is purely `get;`/`set;`/`init;` (plus optional one-line `[...]` attributes above the declaration).
- Removes blank lines between **adjacent** one-line simple auto-properties (including `init` and get-only).
